                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The future of the Albanian regime, the interests of Yugoslavia, Greece, and the
                    Western powers in Albania, and the possibilities which were open to the United
                    States in the area were questions that were considered in the Policy Planning
                    Staff’s paper P.P.S. 60, September <pb facs="0325" n="311" xml:id="pg_311"/> 12,
                    “Yugoslav-Moscow Controversy as Related to U.S. Foreign Policy Objectives”, <ref
                        target="#pg_947">page 947</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
